	<region id="editorData">
		<node id="editorData">
			<attribute id="HowToTrigger" type="LSString" value="Repro steps:&#xD;&#xA;1. Start the game.&#xD;&#xA;2. loadlevel WLD_Main_A&#xD;&#xA;3. oe readyattackonden&#xD;&#xA;4. Blow the horn and side with the tieflings (kill all goblin).&#xD;&#xA;5. goto 260.71, 14.82, 523.32&#xD;&#xA;6. Talk with Halsin.&#xD;&#xA;7. Skip through the dialog with Kagha.&#xD;&#xA;8. Talk with Halsin again.&#xD;&#xA;or&#xD;&#xA;1. Start the game&#xD;&#xA;2. oe readygoblinhuntvictory&#xD;&#xA;3.  goto 207; 465&#xD;&#xA;4. Talk to Zevlor, skip the dialogue but he needs to stay.&#xD;&#xA;5. goto 259; 520&#xD;&#xA;6. Talk to Halsin and skip the dialogue.&#xD;&#xA;7. Talk to Halsin again." />
			<attribute id="needLayout" type="bool" value="False" />
			<attribute id="nextNodeId" type="uint32" value="978" />
			<attribute id="synopsis" type="LSString" value="The Druid Grove has been saved (because either the attacking force was repelled or its leaders were assassinated) and Halsin returns. He thanks the player and reacts to events that may have transpired in the grove during his absence. He's previously promised to help the player with their tadpole problem, but he defers this discussion until the next morning after the victory celebrations." />
